{"created-date": {"value": 1684398073747}, "last-modified-date": {"value": 1684398073747}, "source": {"source-orcid": {"uri": "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-9785-7726", "path": "0000-0002-9785-7726", "host": "orcid.org"}, "source-client-id": null, "source-name": {"value": "Luca Baldini"}, "assertion-origin-orcid": null, "assertion-origin-client-id": null, "assertion-origin-name": null}, "put-code": 135299872, "path": "/0000-0002-9785-7726/work/135299872", "title": {"title": {"value": "Accretion geometry of the neutron star low mass X-ray binary Cyg X-2 from X-ray polarization measurements"}, "subtitle": null, "translated-title": null}, "journal-title": {"value": "Monthly Notices of the Royal Astronomical Society"}, "short-description": "<jats:title>ABSTRACT</jats:title>\n               <jats:p>We report spectro-polarimetric results of an observational campaign of the bright neutron star low-mass X-ray binary Cyg X-2 simultaneously observed by IXPE, NICER, and INTEGRAL. Consistently with previous results, the broad-band spectrum is characterized by a lower-energy component, attributed to the accretion disc with kTin \u2248 1\u00a0keV, plus unsaturated Comptonization in thermal plasma with temperature kTe\u00a0= 3\u00a0keV and optical depth \u03c4 \u2248 4, assuming a slab geometry. We measure the polarization degree in the 2\u20138\u00a0keV band P\u00a0= 1.8\u00a0\u00b1\u00a00.3\u00a0per\u2009cent and polarization angle \u03d5\u00a0= 140\u00b0 \u00b1 4\u00b0, consistent with the previous X-ray polarimetric measurements by OSO-8 as well as with the direction of the radio jet which was earlier observed from the source. While polarization of the disc spectral component is poorly constrained with the IXPE data, the Comptonized emission has a polarization degree P\u00a0= 4.0\u00a0\u00b1\u00a00.7\u00a0per\u2009cent and a polarization angle aligned with the radio jet. Our results strongly favour a spreading layer at the neutron star surface as the main source of the polarization signal. However, we cannot exclude a significant contribution from reflection off the accretion disc, as indicated by the presence of the iron fluorescence line.</jats:p>", "citation": {"citation-type": "bibtex", "citation-value": "@article{Farinelli_2022,\tdoi = {10.1093/mnras/stac3726},\turl = {https://doi.org/10.1093%2Fmnras%2Fstac3726},\tyear = 2022,\tmonth = {dec},\tpublisher = {Oxford University Press ({OUP})},\tvolume = {519},\tnumber = {3},\tpages = {3681--3690},\tauthor = {R Farinelli and S Fabiani and J Poutanen and F Ursini and C Ferrigno and S Bianchi and M Cocchi and F Capitanio and A De~Rosa and A Gnarini and F Kislat and G Matt and R Mikusincova and F Muleri and I Agudo and L A Antonelli and M Bachetti and L Baldini and W H Baumgartner and R Bellazzini and S D Bongiorno and R Bonino and A Brez and N Bucciantini and S Castellano and E Cavazzuti and S Ciprini and E Costa and E Del~Monte and L Di~Gesu and N Di~Lalla and A Di~Marco and I Donnarumma and V Doroshenko and M Dov{\\v{c}}iak and S R Ehlert and T Enoto and Y Evangelista and R Ferrazzoli and J A Garcia and S Gunji and K Hayashida and J Heyl and W Iwakiri and S G Jorstad and V Karas and T Kitaguchi and J J Kolodziejczak and H Krawczynski and F La~Monaca and L Latronico and I Liodakis and S Maldera and A Manfreda and F Marin and A P Marscher and H L Marshall and I Mitsuishi and T Mizuno and C-Y Ng and S L O'Dell and N Omodei and C Oppedisano and A Papitto and G G Pavlov and A L Peirson and M Perri and M Pesce-Rollins and P O Petrucci and M Pilia and A Possenti and S Puccetti and B D Ramsey and J Rankin and A Ratheesh and R W Romani and C Sgr{\\`{o}} and P Slane and P Soffitta and G Spandre and T Tamagawa and F Tavecchio and R Taverna and Y Tawara and A F Tennant and N E Thomas and F Tombesi and A Trois and S S Tsygankov and R Turolla and J Vink and M C Weisskopf and K Wu and F Xie and S Zane},\ttitle = {Accretion geometry of the neutron star low mass X-ray binary Cyg X-2 from X-ray polarization